WRITING.TITLE: b'Shut down the negative thoughts'
WRITING.TEXT.Element:Text: I've been struggling a lot more lately and tonight I was stressed and came so so close to going to the grocery to get something easy to b/p. Instead I called a friend and walked to the rock climbing gym to boulder for a while then had a protein shake. It's a tiny step, but it's been really hard for me to get out of the rut and familiarity of going back to food and purging when I'm stressed. Tonight was the first time in a while I felt like I was in control of my ED thoughts instead of them controlling me, and it feels like just maybe there's still some hope for me.
